					<additions><p>First flyleaf: an erased seal. Flyleaf: an English note in the hand of <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_37074791">Henry Bradshaw</persName> gives details of the collation (of quires). F.1r: the seal of Polier (1181). F.1v: a note states the work was written (i.e. composed) by Abū al-Faẓl. The manuscript contains numerous charts in red and black, e.g. ff.44-49 (prices of ingredients for recipes) and ff.75-9 (weaponry).</p> 
